Function dot_product(v1, v2: list of IR): IR
1. Set ps to zero.
2. For i = 1 to length(v1):
   a. Set ps to ps + v1[i]*v2[i].
3. End For
4. Return ps.
End Function

Algorithm determine_orthogonality_using_function
1. For i = 1 to n:
   a. Input v1 and v2, two vectors of IR.
   b. Set ps to dot_product(v1, v2).
   c. If ps = 0, output "The vectors are orthogonal."
      Else, output "The vectors are not orthogonal."
2. End For
End Algorithm
